    <p>Ms. JOLESSA GUZMAN (Student, P.S. 75): They just popped it up in their mind. I don't - they didn't even rehearse for that. </p>
    <p>Ms. CALISTA CONDILI (Student, P.S. 75): Exactly. </p>
    <p>LUNDEN: And Calista finds herself inspired. </p>
    <p>Ms. CONDILI: When I am in fifth grade, I would like to play in Carnegie Hall and hear all the people clap just for me. </p>
    <p>LUNDEN: Nathan Schram says working with the kids thus far has been inspiring for him, too. </p>
