    <p>Mr. MOJULE: Look at Juba, the biggest village in the whole world - no water system, not toilet, no nothing. Huh? Now we need development. </p>
    <p>LANGFITT: This is Southerner's biggest complaint. They say the North exploited their resources - including oil  then neglected the region. </p>
    <p>A few miles from the rally's excitement, the mood is more sober. And Southern Sudan's dire poverty and challenges come into relief. </p>
