    <p>STEVE INSKEEP, Host: </p>
    <p>NPR's Don Gonyea reports.</p>
    <p>(SOUNDBITE OF A CROWD)</p>
    <p>DON GONYEA: It was one final day of campaigning yesterday ahead of today's vote at the RNC's annual winter meeting. In the wide corridor of a hotel convention complex just outside Washington, Michael Steele seemed relaxed as he worked to hang onto his job. He walks as he talks.</p>
