    <p>Unidentified Man: Packers win. Come on. </p>
    <p>Unidentified Woman: Yeah, Packers win. Yeah. </p>
    <p>Unidentified Man: Yeah. </p>
    <p>(Soundbite of laughter) </p>
    <p>QUIRMBACH: Any line between Packers and Bears territory blurs even further about 15 miles to the northwest, in the small town of Silver Lake, Wisconsin. In a bar painted green on the outside called the Packer Inn, Bert Iruk of Evanston, Illinois is halfway through a beer. He offers to sing the Bears fight song. </p>
