    <p>Mr. KOTOK: A big shock, like a $150 oil price or a bird flu pandemic or a war in Iran. </p>
    <p>ARNOLD: As far as average investors, Kotok says the Dow at 12,000 signals something else: if people got scared and pulled money out of stocks - and a lot of people did that - and now they want to get back in... </p>
