    <p>NPR national political correspondent Don Gonyea has this postcard. </p>
    <p>DON GONYEA: It's not particularly easy to get to Manitowoc, Wisconsin, especially in January when you never know what the weather will be like. But there was President Obama on the morning after his State of the Union address. </p>
    <p>(Soundbite of cheering and applause) </p>
    <p>President BARACK OBAMA: Hello, everybody. </p>
    <p>(Soundbite of cheering) </p>
